# Keep configuration files
!pyproject.toml
!setup.py
!setup.cfg
!tox.ini
!Makefile
!Dockerfile
!docker-compose.yaml

# ============================================================================
# NOTES AND GUIDELINES
# ============================================================================

# PRIORITY RULES:
# 1. NEVER commit secrets or credentials (API keys, tokens, passwords)
# 2. NEVER commit large data files (> 100MB) - use Git LFS or external storage
# 3. NEVER commit generated build artifacts (use `make clean`)
# 4. NEVER commit IDE-specific settings (personal preferences)
# 5. NEVER commit test/coverage outputs (generated locally)

# WHAT GETS COMMITTED:
# - Source code (.py files)
# - Tests and fixtures
# - Configuration templates (*.example)
# - Documentation (.md files)
# - Project metadata (pyproject.toml, etc.)

# WHAT DOESN'T GET COMMITTED:
# - Compiled files (__pycache__, *.pyc)
# - Virtual environments (.venv/)
# - Cache directories (.pytest_cache, .mypy_cache, etc.)
# - Secrets and credentials (.env, *.secret*)
# - Build outputs (build/, dist/, *.egg-info/)
# - Large data files (> 100MB)
# - IDE settings (personal .vscode/ or .idea/ files)
# - Log files (*.log)
# - Temporary files (*.tmp, *.bak)

# TO DEBUG THIS FILE:
# Show what files would be ignored:
#   git check-ignore -v <filepath>
#
# Show all ignored files in repo:
#   git ls-files -o -i --exclude-standard
#
# Unignore a file if accidentally ignored:
#   Add `!filename` rule after the ignore rule
#
# Temporarily add ignored file:
#   git add -f filename
#

# LARGE FILE HANDLING:
# If you need to commit large files (> 50MB):
# 1. Install Git LFS: https://git-lfs.github.com/
# 2. Add pattern: `git lfs track "*.parquet"`
# 3. Commit: `git add .gitattributes <file>`
#

# ============================================================================
# DOCUMENTATION AND PROJECT-SPECIFIC NOTES
# ============================================================================

# This .gitignore file ensures:
# ✓ Clean git history (only source and essential files)
# ✓ No accidental commits of secrets/credentials
# ✓ No large data files in repository
# ✓ No IDE or machine-specific files
# ✓ Repository stays lightweight and cloneable
# ✓ Faster clone and fetch operations
# ✓ Reduced storage requirements

# For more information:
# - Git ignore documentation: https://git-scm.com/docs/gitignore
# - GitHub gitignore templates: https://github.com/github/gitignore
# - Stochastic Transit Router docs: /docs/operations/repository_management.md

